1.2.2 Make formulae

Using \(\LaTeX\) construct the formulae for

  1. Accuracy
  2. Detection rate
  3. False alarm rate
  4. Precision

Latex Example: See (http://www.stat.cmu.edu/~cshalizi/rmarkdown/#elements-of-math-mode)

\[ \begin{eqnarray} P(|X-\mu| > k) & = & P(|X-\mu|^2 > k^2)\\ & \leq & \frac{\mathbb{E}\left[|X-\mu|^2\right]}{k^2}\\ & \leq & \frac{\mathrm{Var}[X]}{k^2} \end{eqnarray} \]
